###############################################
# 12. NOTES ON RECID BEHAVIOR
###############################################

# IMPORTANT NOTES:
# 1. All GET endpoints only return records with RECID='*' (unresolved issues)
# 2. Records with RECID='1' (resolved) are NOT shown in any endpoint
# 3. RECID automatically changes from '*' to '1' during re-screening if issue is resolved
# 4. Users cannot manually change RECID (no PUT/DELETE endpoints)
# 5. Data is only inserted/updated through screening process
# 6. UPDTIME is preserved when RECID changes from '*' to '1'

